---
title: Ginger Beef Stir-Fry with Snappy Asparagus
description: A HelloFresh classic! Tender beef and crisp, springy asparagus are quickly stir-fried with warming ginger and served over fluffy basmati rice. Hoisin sauce adds a touch of sweetness and an incredible umami depth. It’s so sweet and succulent, we’re sure you’ll agree with us that this is a recipe worth visiting again and again.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w08-r02-731bfbb1.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w08-r02-4aeab857.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 690 mg
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/ginger-beef-stir-fry-5873bb3db32fbe1a1b00abe2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring @water{1 1/2%cups} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a small #pot{}. Trim and discard bottom inch from @asparagus{6%ounce}, then cut stalks into 2-inch pieces. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.

Once water is boiling, add @basmati rice{3/4%cup} to #pot{}, cover, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered.

Meanwhile, whisk together garlic, ginger, @soy sauce{1/2%ounce}, 1 TBSP water, and 2 TBSP @hoisin sauce{1%jar} (we sent more) in a small #bowl{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Pat @beef sirloin tips{12%ounce} dry with a paper towel, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and toss until nearly cooked to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add asparagus and scallions to same pan over medium heat. (TIP: If veggies seem dry, add a drizzle of oil.) Cook until tender but still crunchy, ~{3-4%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Add steak tips and sauce to pan and cook until sauce is thickened and meat reaches desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide between plates, then top with stir-fry and garnish with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.